# XemoToken

XemoToken is a Move-based token project designed to demonstrate the capabilities of the Aptos blockchain. This project includes a set of tests to ensure the correct functionality of the token, including minting, transferring, and burning tokens.


## Installation

To get started with XemoToken, you need to have the Aptos CLI installed. Follow the instructions below to install the CLI and set up the project.

### Install Aptos CLI

1. **Download the Aptos CLI**:
   - For macOS:
     ```sh
     brew install aptos
     ```
   - For Linux:
     ```sh
     wget https://github.com/aptos-labs/aptos-core/releases/download/latest/aptos-cli-ubuntu-latest.zip
     unzip aptos-cli-ubuntu-latest.zip -d /usr/local/bin
     ```
   - For Windows:
     Download the latest release from the [Aptos GitHub Releases](https://github.com/aptos-labs/aptos-core/releases) and add it to your PATH.

2. **Verify the installation**:
   ```sh
   aptos --version
   ```

### Clone the Repository

Clone the XemoToken repository to your local machine:

aptos move compile
aptos move test
aptos move publish

### Run
aptos move run --function-id 'my_address::Xemo::mint' --args 'u64:<AMOUNT>'
aptos move run --function-id 'my_address::Xemo::transfer' --args 'address:<RECIPIENT_ADDRESS>' 'u64:<AMOUNT>'
